a.xlink:title: Consideration, such as amount of money, paid or received in exchange for an asset that has been invested, loaned or borrowed for a certain period. The interest is expressed as a fixed amount or percentage of the amount upon which the interest is applied.
Set of parameters used to calculate an interest amount.

Definition of the cash proceeds for a corporate action in generic terms; that is, before applying it to specific securities holding. An example would be the definition of a dividend payment where all the information will be given in general on a per share basis.
Process of lending or borrowing cash or securities against securities or cash collateral. It aims at optimising liquidity, support a trading strategy, or increase settlement efficiency.
Amount of money due to the government or tax authority, according to various pre-defined parameters such as thresholds or income.
Posting of an item to a cash account, in the context of a cash transaction, that results in an increase or decrease to the balance of the account.
Management of interest which consists into calculating the interest, requesting its payment or distributing the interest proceeds.
Amount of an undertaking such as a guarantee or standby letter of credit.
Specifies the conditions for overdraft on the account or for positive amounts.
Settlement of the securities in a securities transaction, that is, the instruction to deliver or receive securities, involving the payment of an amount of money or not.
Information related to a non-standardised identification, such as a proprietary party identification or account identification.
Specifies in terms of value and quantity the assets.

An arrangement in which a lender gives money or property to a borrower, and the borrower agrees to return the property or repay the money, usually along with interest, at some future point(s) in time.
Numerical representation of the net increases and decreases in an account at a specific point in time.
Agreement between an account servicer and an account owner about the services linked to an account.
Calculation of the net asset value for an investment fund/fund class.
Electronic money product that provides the cardholder with a portable and specialised computer device that typically contains a microprocessor.
